[{'comment_id': 901054783, 'comment_body': "There's no need to use the mainDispatcher to show the ProgressBar as we are already on the main thread(because of Activity.lifecycleScope). If this method were to get called from another thread it will immediately fail as we are accessing a view from a background thread.

```
) {
    deckPicker.showProgressBar()
    var exception: Throwable? = null
    // rest of the method
```", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 19, 6, 29, 40, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'lukstbit', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 901055815, 'comment_body': 'I would prefer that we keep using `try/catch` instead of `runCatching`. Also, as we look for the general Exception type, I think it would be better to add a check for the exception being a `CancellationException` and rethrow it if it is. This way we guard against the code inside `downgradeCollection()` being migrated to coroutines, throwing CancellationException and us catching that exception. More info about this can be found [here](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/cancellation-and-timeouts.html#cancellation-is-cooperative):

```
} catch (e: Exception) {
    if (e is CancellationException) {
        throw e
    }
    Timber.w(e)
    mException = e
}
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 19, 6, 40, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'lukstbit', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 902573243, 'comment_body': 'What about the comment present in the previous code: "It would be great if we could catch the OutOfSpaceException here"?

